snippet.title: Baahubali - The Epic Release Trailer (Telugu) | Prabhas, Rana | SS Rajamouli | 31st October 2025
snippet.description:
#BaahubaliTheEpic is a combined narrative of the two-part Indian film saga, weaving together the grandeur and drama of Baahubali: The Beginning and Baahubali: The Conclusion into one epic tale.

CAST

Prabhas as Sivudu & Baahubali, Rana Daggubati as Bhallaladeva, Anushka Shetty as Devasena, Tamannaah as Avanthika with Ramya Krishna, Nasser, Sathyaraj, Kiccha Sudeepa, Adivi Sesh, Rakesh Varre, Meka Ramakrishna.

CREW

Screenplay & Direction: S.S. Rajamouli
Presented by: K. Raghavendra Rao B.A.
Producers: Shobu Yarlagadda & Prasad Devineni
Story: V. Vijayendra Prasad 
DOP: K.K. Senthil Kumar
Production Designer: Sabu Cyril
Music Composer: M.M. Keeravaani
VFX Supervision: V. Srinivas Mohan
Sound Design: P.M. Satheesh
Stunt Choreography: Peter Hein
Additional Stunts: King Solomon, Lee Whittakar, Kaloyan Vodenicharov
Dance Choreographers: Prem Rakshit, Shankar, Dinesh Kumar, Jani
Editor: Tammiraju 
Costume Designer: Rama Rajamouli, Prashanti Tripirneni 
Dialogues:
Telugu - C.H. Vijay Kumar, Ajay Kumar G
Hindi - Manoj Muntashir
Tamil - Karky
DI & Sound Mix: Annapurna  Studios
Marketing: Walls & Trends

snippet.title: Hind Ki Chadar | An Ode of Reverence & Sacrifice of Sri Guru Teg Bahadur Ji By Satinder Sartaaj
snippet.description:
#hindkichadar #gurutegbhadurji #satindersartaaj 

On The Sacred Occasion of THE 350th MARTYRDOM DAY of SRI GURU TEG BAHADUR JI, We're Presenting our Tribute "Hind Ki Chadar" | à¨¹à¨¿à©°à¨¦ à¨•à©€ à¨šà¨¾à¨¦à¨° | à¤¹à¤¿à¤‚à¤¦ à¤•à¥€ à¤šà¤¾à¤¦à¤° By Satinder Sartaaj. 

The legacy of Guru Tegh Bahadur Ji, the Ninth Guru of the Sikhs, radiates as an unfading constellation of courage, sacrifice, and eternal truth. Revered as â€œHind Ki Chadarâ€ â€” the Sacred Shield of India, His supreme martyrdom did not belong to one faith alone, but became a benediction for all humanity â€” safeguarding freedom of conscience, the sanctity of belief, and the dignity of the human spirit.

In this devotional offering, Dr. Satinder Sartaaj gathers the fragrance of centuries into verse, tracing the divine journey of the Guru â€” from His serene birth in Guru-ke-Mahal to the transcendent moment in Delhi, where His luminous spirit embraced martyrdom and transformed Chandni Chowk into a sanctified ground of remembrance.
